cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper presents a real-time full duplex radio system for 5G wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the challenge of canceling self-interference in full duplex radios, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and signal processing. 

3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The design of a full duplex radio system involves control and optimization of various components, such as the analog and digital parts, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 

4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the throughput achieved by the proposed full duplex system, which is a performance metric relevant to multimedia applications. 

5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper prototypes the full duplex radio system on a software-defined radio (SDR) platform, which involves hardware architecture design and implementation.
